@Node How_To_Use_Help "Organiser Help: How To Use Help"
@ToC Main
@{B}How To Use Help@{UB}

You can ask for help in several ways:
@{B}Help key:@{UB} Press the Help key to see Help contents.

@{B}Help icon:@{UB} Click the Help icon (?) for Help contents.

@{B}Help menu:@{UB} Choose a topic from the Help menu.

@{B}Menu help:@{UB} For Help with a menu or menu command, hold down the
the Right Mouse key over the menu or command and press the Help
key.

Requester help: For Help with a requester press the Help key
while the requester is highlighted. Due to operating system
requirements, this does not work with @{" file requesters " Link FileRequester} or
system requesters.


@{fg highlight}Help Menu Commands@{fg text}

@{" How Do I...?    " Link How_Do_I}  Shows a list of explanatory functions (for
example, 'How to add a Birthday').

@{" How To Use Help " Link How_To_Use_Help}  Shows these instructions.

@{" Contents        " Link Main}  Shows the Table of Contents.

@{" Tutorial        " Link Tutorial}  Shows the Tutorial section which contains
detailed information on using Organiser for beginners and
advanced users.

@{" Shortcuts       " Link Shortcuts}  Shows a list of available keyboard shortcuts.

@{" Index           " Link Org_Index}  Shows all Organiser commands.

@{" Troubleshooting " Link Troubleshooting}  Shows common problems and their solutions.
@EndNode



